article.headline: High Point 73, Elon University 71
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 18 points on field goals and had six rebounds to lead High Point to a 73-71 win Wednesday over host Elon. Justin Dunn had 15, Issa Konare had 14 and Akeem Scott scored 11 to help High Point (5-2) to the win. High Point held the lead 36-32 at the half and scored 19 points off of turnovers. Elon's high scorer was Jackson Atoyebi with 16 points and 10 rebounds for the 2-6 Phoenix. Montell Watson scored 14 points and Brett James had 11 points. High Point's Panthers were in the first of a five-game road schedule against Elon and was fresh from a 103-61 win over Ferrum from Saturday.
